  <div class="term-glossary">
    <h3>URI (Uniform Resource Identifier):</h3>
    <p>It is a short string that uniquely identifies a resource (service, page, document, email, encyclopedia, etc.). Usually these resources are accessible on a network or system. The URI can be Uniform Resource Locators (URLs), Uniform Resource Name (URN), or both (URL + URN).
  </p>

